homepage.title.message: Desktop AI Humanoid Robot Open Source Ecosystem - Open Source Otto Robot

homepage.description.message: Otto DIY robot is an open-source Arduino robot project designed for education and STEM learning, providing complete build guides and programming tutorials

homepage.meetRobot.message: Meet Tenengla Technology's AI Desktop Humanoid Robot

homepage.intro1.message: Tenengla Technology's R&D team combines 3D printing with the concept of creating everything with electronic components, allowing beginners to build their own desktop AI robot in just 30 minutes at ultra-low cost! Through a cloud-integrated architecture, the desktop robot is equipped with AI voice dialogue, AI motion feedback, AI vision system and other capabilities. The product deeply integrates multiple scenarios such as emotional companionship, maker education, 3D printing, AI large models, embodied intelligence, and smart home. It supports one-click integration with mainstream AI services such as Tenengla AI, Xiaozhi AI, Tuya Smart, and Volcano Engine. It is an intelligent ecosystem hardware platform for AI desktop robots. Through this website, you can learn how to build, program, and extend your own desktop robot.

homepage.intro2.message: This website currently only shares desktop AI robot building documentation written by {xiaopeng} and {qiaodan}

features.easyToLearn.description.message: The AI desktop robot features a simple design using common components, making it perfect for beginners. Even without electronics or programming experience, you can quickly complete the build.

features.openSource.description.message: As a fully open-source project, this robot supports free modification and extension. You can add sensors, change the appearance, or develop new features to create your own custom robot.

features.stemEducation.description.message: This robot integrates multidisciplinary knowledge including mechanics, electronics, programming, and 3D printing, making it an ideal educational tool for inspiring student creativity and developing problem-solving skills.
